ownedComment.body: Overview of Party package classes (both of 19152 Part 1 and 19152 Part 2).
Overview of Administrative package classes (both of 19152 Part 1 and 19152 Part 2).
Overview of Spatial Unit package classes (both of 19152 Part 1 and 19152 Part 2).
Overview of Surveying and Representation package classes of 19152 Part 2.

invariant {Instances of LA_Right and LA_Responisbility have always one (= 1) party. Sometimes there can be 0 or 1 party; e.g. no (= 0) party for object restriction and 1 party for right restriction (indicated by partyRequired boolean attribute)}
Each spatial unit has a dimension. There can be a 2D spatial unit, or a 3D spatial unit, with a spatial unit with dimension "liminal" in between. See Annex B.
invariant {If dimension = 3D than structure in LA_Level can be topological, polygon, unstructured or point}
invariant {if dimension=2D then volume not specified if dimension=3D then area not specified}
See Annex B for a more detailed description of boundary face strings and boundary faces.

For polygon-based (2D) or polyhedron-based (3D) spatial units: no minus and at least one plus, for topology based spatial units: at least one plus or minus. New in LADM II: Alternatively, spatial unit geometries (2D or 3D) may be stored directly in the geometry attribute (optional, data type:Geometry).
invariant {Party can only have 0 RRR in case the party has specific role}
Topology relationship ISO19107_Type as defined in ISO 19107:2019.
invariant {share must be specified, unless this is meaningless for the specific type (indicated by shareCheck=false; in this case constraint 'sum (RRR.share) = 1 per type' cannot be applied)}
invariant {If structure = text then geometry/topology is optional}
